<div id="outline-container-orgace8d00" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgace8d00">Overview</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgace8d00">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><b>Difficulty:</b> Very easy</li>
<li><b>Time</b>: 45 to 50 minutes</li>
<li><b>Cleaning effort</b>: Very easy</li>
<li><b>Good with</b>: Soup, tangy dal (tomato, mango, etc) and rasam.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgdfb998e" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgdfb998e">Ingredients</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgdfb998e">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Tilapia fish fillets (frozen works too).</li>
<li>Lemon juice</li>
<li>Red chilli powder</li>
<li>Turmeric</li>
<li>Salt</li>
<li>Ginger + garlic paste</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgaefe60a" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgaefe60a">Preparation</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgaefe60a">
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>Add lemon juice to tilapia fillets. Mix them well.</li>
<li>All all the spices and evently coat them.</li>
<li>Keep aside for 30 minutes for marination.</li>
<li>Take a wide pan (cast iron is perfet!), add oil and heat
it in <b>medium heat</b>.</li>
<li>Fry on both sides of tilapia fillets until they are red, and
have small charred brown spots on each side.</li>
<li>Enjoy!</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>

